text: The banded flying frog or banded tree frog (Leptomantis fasciatus) is a frog. It lives in Malaysia, Indonesia, and Brunei. People have seen it as high as 200 meters above sea level. This frog lives in peat swamps in rainforests forests. Scientists believe that this frog does not live in places that human beings have changed. The tadpoles swim in the swamp. Scientists believe this frog is not in danger of dying out because it lives in such a large place. The frog lives in three protected parks: Gunung Mulu National Park, Kayan Mentarang National Park, and Ulu Temberong National Park. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Leptomantis fasciatus
